{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3297977,"name":"Floyd Moore","username":"feverittm","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/feverittm/{size}/4928_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-30T17:50:51.386Z","cooked":"<p>I know this subject has been brought up before, but I have never seen a reasonable solution to the problem.<br>
Our team uses NEO motors almost exclusively.  This means that for simulation we need to deal with the SparkMax.<br>
We have tried using the Rev simulation interface, but it has a number of known issues.<br>
I believe the current best solution would be some form of ‘Mock’ for the SparkMax that would operate in simulation mode.  Even a very ‘dumb’ motor controller Mock would be nice at this point.<br>
I know that some teams have done this in the past (including YAGSL), but I wanted to ask if someone has a more generic solution to this issue.</p>
